<body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; padding: 20px;">
  <h1>Privacy Policy for QuickStash</h1>
  <p>Last updated: July 5, 2025</p>

  <p>QuickStash ("we", "our", or "us") operates the QuickStash mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share information in connection with your use of the App.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Personal Information: name, address, email, phone number, and payment details (handled securely by Stripe).</li>
    <li>Device Information: IP address, location, and browser/device type.</li>
    <li>App Usage Data: order history, preferences, interactions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To process orders and deliveries</li>
    <li>To connect you with couriers</li>
    <li>To improve service and support</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>With couriers fulfilling orders</li>
    <li>With Stripe for payments</li>
    <li>With authorities if legally required</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You may request access to or deletion of your data by contacting us at <strong>support@quickstash.com</strong>.</p>

  <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This app is not intended for users under 13. We do not knowingly collect their data.</p>

  <h2>6. Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy and will notify users of material changes.</p>

  <h2>7. Contact</h2>
  <p>support@quickstash.com</p>
